Description: Very windy conditions with snow and then rain today. Also higher than normal water levels along the coast. Maximum wind gusts: 80 km/h. Total snowfall: 5 to 10 cm Prince and Kings counties. 15 cm Prince county. Time span for storm surge: within 2 hours of noon. High tide: peaking near noon today. Remarks: Snow is expected to change to rain this morning. Strong easterly winds will also diminish later this morning. In addition, very low pressure will coincide with very large spring tides to produce significantly elevated water levels. This may produce some minor flooding, especially along shorelines exposed to the east. A snowfall warning is in effect for Prince County. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to PEstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #PEStorm.
